From: Gravio <gravio@uni-muenster.de>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 14:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feature_subsets refactor step 3: extract per-video
 orchestration
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Following AUDIT_feature_subsets_calculator.md, this is step 3 of the
refactoring plan (step 2 was rolled into step 1 since no kernel-level
bugs surfaced during extraction).

Goal: pull the body of `FeatureSubsetsCalculator.run()`'s per-video
loop into a module-level function `process_one_video`, so the per-
video work has no dependence on `self` state and is therefore:
- Easier to reason about (all inputs are explicit parameters)
- Easier to test (no need to instantiate the full class)
- Picklable for future cross-process work (step 6)

What changed:

1. NEW: mufasa/feature_extractors/feature_subset_orchestration.py
   Module-level orchestration:

     @dataclass(frozen=True)
     class VideoProcessingConfig:
         feature_families: List[str]
         file_type: str
         temp_dir: str
         two_point_combs: np.ndarray
         within_animal_three_point_combs: Mapping[str, np.ndarray]
         within_animal_four_point_combs: Mapping[str, np.ndarray]
         animal_bps: Mapping[str, list]
         roi_dict: Optional[Mapping[str, dict]] = None
         video_info_df: Optional[pd.DataFrame] = None

     def process_one_video(
         file_path: str,
         config: VideoProcessingConfig,
         file_idx: int = 0,
         n_total_files: int = 1,
         print_progress: bool = True,
     ) -> str: ...

   process_one_video reads the per-video pose dataframe, clips
   coords to frame bounds, runs each requested feature family
   kernel, builds the results DataFrame with the legacy
   _FEATURE_SUBSET suffix and sorted columns, writes to the
   temp file path, and returns the save path.

   Two helper functions in the orchestration module:
     - _read_video_info_for: looks up px_per_mm, fps, resolution
       from the video_info dataframe (mirrors the validation
       logic of ConfigReader.read_video_info but doesn't need
       `self`)
     - _clip_pose_coords_to_frame: same coord clipping that was
       previously inline in the per-video loop

   The dataclass is frozen so it can be used as a dict key (useful
   for cross-process work in step 6) and signals immutability.

2. MODIFIED: mufasa/feature_extractors/feature_subsets.py
   - Added _build_video_processing_config() helper method that
     builds a VideoProcessingConfig from current self state. This
     is the single source of truth for what state crosses the
     class → orchestration boundary.
   - run() loop body replaced with a one-line call to
     process_one_video(). The loop iteration is still in the
     class for now (step 6 will wrap it in a process pool).
   - Removed dead per-family methods (9 of them, ~90 lines):
       _get_two_point_bp_distances
       __get_three_point_angles
       __get_three_point_hulls
       __get_four_point_hulls
       __get_convex_hulls
       __get_framewise_movement
       __get_roi_center_distances
       __get_distances_to_frm_edge
       __get_inside_roi
     These were thin delegators added in step 1; no longer needed
     since process_one_video calls the kernels directly.
   - Removed now-dead imports: kernel functions, SimbaTimer.
     (read_df, pd, np still used by the __append_* methods.)

3. MODIFIED: tests/smoke_feature_kernels.py
   - Replaced case 7 (which checked the dead delegate methods
     existed) with three new cases:
       Case 7: those methods are GONE
       Case 8: orchestration module exports VideoProcessingConfig
         and process_one_video at top level
       Case 9: process_one_video has the right signature (no `self`,
         takes config and file_path)
   - Test count: 9/9 cases passed (was 7/7).

Verified in sandbox:
- All three .py files compile
- 9/9 smoke_feature_kernels tests pass
- All other smoke tests still pass

Verified ON USER'S WORKSTATION (TODO):
- tests/smoke_feature_kernels_realdata.py against a real per-video
  reference output. This is the gold-standard byte-equivalence
  check for the entire refactor.

What this does NOT change:
- Public API: FeatureSubsetsCalculator(...).run() works exactly as
  before. External callers (mufasa.ui.*, mufasa.ui_qt.forms.features)
  see no difference.
- Per-video output: byte-identical to the previous version. Same
  column names, same value ordering, same _FEATURE_SUBSET suffix.
- Sequential execution: still one video at a time. The class loops
  through self.data_paths and calls process_one_video for each.

Subtle behavior changes (one):
- Per-video progress print now uses len(self.data_paths) for the
  Video N/M denominator. Previously the per-family progress line
  used len(self.outlier_corrected_paths), which was a typo —
  outlier_corrected_paths is a ConfigReader attribute that points
  to the same set of files when data_dir is None but could differ
  when an explicit data_dir is passed. The new code uses the
  active data_paths consistently. If someone was relying on
  outlier_corrected_paths showing through into the per-family
  progress line specifically, that's now gone (the count is
  correct in the new version).

Not in this patch (planned for follow-up):
- Step 4: split run() from __init__ (move directory creation,
  ROI loading, etc. out of the constructor)
- Step 5: make feature_families an enum
- Step 6: wrap process_one_video loop in ProcessPoolExecutor
  for parallel execution

Each future step is independently shippable.
